Sweet Shop Management System
TEST REPORT :
Submitted by: Chethana S N

Project Title: Sweet Shop Management System

Technologies Used: React.js (Frontend), Express.js (Backend), Prisma ORM, PostgreSQL, Tailwind CSS, JWT Authentication

1. Introduction
The Sweet Shop Management System is a full-stack web application designed to simplify and automate the process of managing a sweet shopâ€™s inventory and sales. The system provides role-based dashboards for Admin and User, enabling efficient sweet management and secure user authentication.
This report documents the testing procedures, results, and conclusions derived from testing both the frontend and backend components of the system.

2. Objectives of Testing
The primary objectives of the testing process were:

1.To ensure each module performs as intended.
2.To verify user and admin authentication flows.
3.To validate the CRUD functionalities for sweet management.
4.To confirm data consistency between the frontend and backend.
5.To verify that role-based access restrictions are enforced securely.
6.To confirm email notifications work properly for password resets.

